## reserved-memory

The `/reserved-memory` node is a parent node for child nodes describing memory regions reserved for specific purposes.

```dts
/* arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/sm8550.dtsi */
reserved-memory {
    #address-cells = <2>;
    #size-cells = <2>;
    ranges;

    rmtfs_mem: memory@f7c00000 {
        compatible = "qcom,rmtfs-memory";
        reg = <0x0 0xf7c00000 0x0 0x280000>;
    };
};
```
